    "excerpt": "--- title: Focus Manager sidebar_label: Focus Manager category: input-interaction --- # Focus Manager `Dali::Ui::FocusManager` controls keyboard focus for `Dali::Ui::View` objects in a dali-ui application. ## Table of Contents - [Getting the Application Focus Manager](#getting-the-application-focus-manager) - [Requesting Focus for Views and Containers](#requesting-focus-for-views-and-containers) - [Moving Focus](#moving-focus) - [Using Focus Groups](#using-focus-groups) - [Customizing the Focus Indicator](#customizing-the-focus-indicator) - [Reacting to Focus Changes](#reacting-to-focus-changes) - [Clearing and Preserving Focus](#clearing-and-preserving-focus) - [Inspecting the Last Focus Change Device](#inspecting-the-last-focus-change-device) ## Getting the Application Focus Manager Use the singleton `Dali::Ui::FocusManager::Get()` when application code needs to request, move, inspect, or clear focus. Store the returned `Dali::Ui::FocusManager` handle where your controller configures focus behavior. `Dali::Ui::FocusManager` is the app-facing focus controller. The focused object exposed by the manager is a `Dali::Ui::View`, so application focus code should keep working with view h"
