    "excerpt": "--- title: Image View sidebar_label: Image View category: views-components --- # Image View `Dali::Ui::ImageView` displays image resources in a dali-ui app. Image loading is asynchronous by default, and the view provides app-facing controls for loading, fitting, sampling, masking, coloring, and N-patch rendering. ## Table of Contents - [Create and Update an Image](#create-and-update-an-image) - [Fit, Crop, and Sample the Image](#fit-crop-and-sample-the-image) - [Use Placeholders and Loading Signals](#use-placeholders-and-loading-signals) - [Control Loading and Resource Lifetime](#control-loading-and-resource-lifetime) - [Apply Color, Alpha, and Masks](#apply-color-alpha-and-masks) - [Use N-Patch Images](#use-n-patch-images) - [Property Constants](#property-constants) ## Create and Update an Image Create an image view with `Dali::Ui::ImageView::New()`, then set the image URL with `SetResourceUrl()`. The fluent setters return `Dali::Ui::ImageView&`, so related image options can be configured in one expression. Use `GetResourceUrl()` when you need to inspect the current image source, and `Reload()` when the current URL should be loaded again after changing loader-time options. `Dali::"
  },
