    "excerpt": "--- title: Label sidebar_label: Label category: views-components --- # Label `Dali::Ui::Label` is the dali-ui view for displaying non-editable text in an application view tree. ## Table of Contents - [Create a Label](#create-a-label) - [Choose Font and Typographic Style](#choose-font-and-typographic-style) - [Control Scale, Line Height, and Direction](#control-scale-line-height-and-direction) - [Handle Anchor Clicks](#handle-anchor-clicks) - [Use Asynchronous Rendering and Render Scale](#use-asynchronous-rendering-and-render-scale) - [Read Label State](#read-label-state) ## Create a Label Use `Dali::Ui::Label::New` to create the text view. The overload `Dali::Ui::Label::New(const Dali::String&)` sets the initial text during construction, so it is the most direct choice for application UI labels. `Dali::Ui::Label` is a `Dali::Ui::View`, so application code can return it, store it, and add it to view-based layouts as part of the dali-ui view tree. ## Choose Font and Typographic Style A label exposes typed setters for common font selection. Use `SetFontFamily`, `SetFontSize`, `SetFontWeight`, `SetFontWidth`, and `SetFontSlant` when the app needs a specific typographic treatment. For v"
