    "excerpt": "--- title: Ui Scale Manager sidebar_label: Ui Scale Manager category: styling-theme-config --- # Ui Scale Manager `Dali::Ui::UiScaleManager` provides access to the shared UI scale used by dali-ui view layout. ## Table of Contents - [Set the Application UI Scale](#set-the-application-ui-scale) - [Read the Current Scale](#read-the-current-scale) - [Work with the Manager Handle](#work-with-the-manager-handle) ## Set the Application UI Scale Use `Dali::Ui::UiScaleManager::Get` to access the singleton scale manager, then call `Dali::Ui::UiScaleManager::SetScale` with the scale factor that should be used by dali-ui layout. In a dali-ui application, your app-facing object tree is made from `Dali::Ui::View` objects; layout roots are registered by the view implementation, so a scale change invalidates registered layout roots and causes the affected view tree to be measured again. A common pattern is to expose a small set of preset scale values from application settings or a developer menu: Pass a positive finite value to `Dali::Ui::UiScaleManager::SetScale`. The current implementation logs an error and keeps the existing scale when the value is `NaN` or non-positive. ## Read the Current Sca"
